We attach a function box to a set of wires by calling a procedurefunction that constructs that kind of box. The arguments to the constructor procedurefunction are the wires to be attached to the box. For example, given that we can construct and-gates, or-gates, and inverters, we can wire together the half-adder shown in Figure:
